2026-03-31T18:47:30.385Z JOY-00B6 comment.added "Root cause: sequential ID generation is not collision-safe in distributed scenarios. Two machines running joy add without sync get the same next ID. Solution: ADR-027 -- append 2 hex digits from title hash to the sequential counter. New format: JOY-0100-5C. Old IDs stay unchanged, no migration needed. Short-form input (JOY-0100) accepted when unambiguous." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
